@node "History" "History"


   @{b}1.4 - February 13th, 1998@{ub}

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} @{"Timer Requests" link "LIST_Timer" 0} and @{"Resident DOS cmds" link "LIST_DOSRes" 0} added to the list types.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Added "Intuition Settings..." to the Tools menu.
       
       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} "PUBSCREEN" argument/tooltype.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Added support for Jason Hulance's @{"Explorer" link "Explorer" 0} (included in 
         this archive along with a pre-made datafile).

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} You can now open a new public screen from the "Screens/Windows" 
         list.  Note that I have no intention of turning SysInspector into 
         a full-featured public screen manager, so don't expect any fancy 
         feature.

       ° Fixed problems with RAM: DOS locks.  The "Scan RAM: locks" prefs 
         option is now gone.

       ° New pictogram for Assigns.

       ° Message Ports priority is now editable.

       ° Iconifying when there was no icon available would use a garbled 
         icon (built-in icon had a wrng PlanePick value).

       ° boards.library 2.17 included (now recognizes 375 boards).

       ° Some changes to the listbrowser V42 support to match with the 
         latest changes in the current beta.

       ° Animated "About" is back for button.gadget V41 (a forecoming 
         update of the gadget will eliminate the flicker).

       ° Fixed potential Enforcer hits when saving prefs would fail.

       ° Now uses 32-bits maths to calculate the largest block percentage 
         in the More window when displaying a memory node.

       ° Saving the content of the More window would display the wrong 
         address for the displayed object if you were using formatted 
         hex values.

       ° Some changes to the Screenmode ModeID sort code, fixing some 
         occasional problems with it.

       ° After signaling a task, will wait for 3 secs instead of just one 
         before checking if it's gone.

       ° Some changes to the "More" display for tasks and processes.

       ° Note that the Warped FTP site is often behind with classes 
         releases.  I advise you check ftp://ftp.thule.no/pub/classact/ 
         instead to obtain the latest ClassAct archive.

       ° I'll be probably be moving during spring '98, so please Email me 
         first before sending me any regular mail or registration fee.


   @{b}1.3 - November 11th, 1997@{ub}

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} @{"ARexx" link "ARexxMenu" 0} port with a complete command set.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} "ARexx" menu, with up to 10 user-defined entries.  Check 
              the new page in the preferences.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} "System Settings..." in the Tools menu.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} "Add" button for "Assigns" and "Memory" lists.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Sortable "Screenmodes" list, and "Locks" are now sorted 
              by names.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Editable library/device OpenCount, by double-clicking on it.

       ° When not using the button array, speedbar.gadget will no longer 
         be opened, and pictograms won't be created, wasting less memory 
         and screen pens in that mode.  Likewise, using the button array 
         won't open chooser.gadget (unless actually required in another 
         window).

       ° You can now change SysInspector's own task priority from the 
         Tasks list.

       ° Closing a public screen will now try to remove any pending lock 
         left after closing all open windows.

       ° Various bugs removed from the Prefs window and the cleanup code.

       ° No longer uses reqtools.library, now uses ClassAct's 
         requester.class and getfile.gadget.  Also included an updated 
         boards.library.

       ° More information shown in the "System" list.

       ° Various enhancements to the More window content.

       ° Various enhancements/fixes to the GUI handling code.

       ° CA prefs now launched async to SI.
       
       ° Added support for the forecoming V42 of listbrowser.gadget.

       ° Recompiled with EC 3.3a.

       ° And probably quite a few more bug fixes here and there.



   @{b}1.2 - June 7th, 1997@{ub}

   Only three registrations so far...  Humm...  You guys better show more 
   support, or I'll simply move on to other projects if nobody feels SI is 
   worth at least 15$ US...


       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Button array alternative for selecting the list type,
              with optional popup help.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Gadtools menu can also be freed when closing a 
              window (or a task with an opened window).
       
       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Added CPU Traps to the "System" list.
       
       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Added a couple of new entries in the preferences.

       ° Uses memory pools during list generation, making it a bit faster 
         and fixing various random crashes happening on some systems.

       ° Improved the "Generate Report...".

       ° More accurate sort method for "Mounts" sorted with volumes first.

       ° "Flush Memory..." now reports how much memory was regained.

       ° Cleaned up the error handling code called if SI would fail to 
         start.

       ° Left/Right cursor keys will change the list type.

       ° boards.library 2.12 included (now recognizes 355 boards).

       ° Dual Playfield Pri-2 would be shown as "DPF" instead of "DPF2" in
         the Screenmode list.
         
       ° Now also display screenmodes that don't have a defined name.
       
       ° 'Remove' and 'Flush' wouldn't work unless you had "Confirm 
         Actions" enabled in the preferences.
       
       ° "System" can detect MBench under "Software".
       
       ° Some changes to various "More" lists.
       
       ° Removed the kludge from the System's Vector display now that 
         LoadV43Module and FastExec can peacefuly coexist.  Make sure you
         have at least V2.7 of FastExec, and don't use the "FREEOLD" option.
       
       ° Removed the address padding kludge for hierarchical lists.  Make 
         sure you have listbrowser.gadget 41.313 or better.

       ° Background CLIs (launched with "Run") will be shown as
         CLI-BGND(<cli#>).
         
       ° Changed the small arrows in hierarchical lists with custom-made 
         ones (both larger and nicer).
         
       ° A couple of other bugs were fixed.



   @{b}1.1 - April 7th, 1997@{ub}

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} TASKPRI argument in the commandline.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} Mounts sort method can be configured.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} "Generate Report..." in the Tools menu.

       ° @{b}NEW:@{ub} "Screenmodes" list type.  You will probably need to
              readjust your "Initial List" setting in your preferences and
              resave.

       ° Had forgotten to put non-Newicon imageries for most icons.  Oops :)

       ° The More window won't unnecessarily refresh itself while disabled.

       ° Added "Largest chunk" to the Memory's More window
       
       ° Expansion boards now shown on two lines, and will also show
         if they're of ZorroII or ZorroIII type.
        
       ° Assign list now supports paths upto 150 chars long (still only the
         first 50 chars displayed).  Should fix the "Fault 120" errors 
         happening too often to those with long path names.
        
       ° SI will stop playing shy and will display its own info in the
         More window when its task is selected.



   @{b}1.0 - March 23th, 1997@{ub}

       ° First Aminet release.



   @{b}ß0.050 - December 29th, 1996@{ub}

       ° First public beta release.





 "I don't think I'm amazing
  In fact, I'm quite insane
  To live inside my bucket
  With all my plastic chains."

      - Ozzy Osbourne.
@endnode

@node "Others" "Other Programs I wrote"
  Other programs that I wrote:

        @{b}° CAMP 1.2@{ub} - ClassAct Mp3 Player is a small GUI front-end
                     for Stéphane Tavenard's mpega, an mp3 audio decoder.

        @{b}° DevsMan 1.4@{ub} - Devs: directory manager, allow easy handling 
                        for your DOSDrivers, Datatypes, etc...

        @{b}° FileScroller 3.40@{ub} - File lister for TransAmiga BBS (3.50 and up
                              for Excelsior! BBS.)

        @{b}° LowFrag 1.3@{ub} - Small system patch that helps reducing memory
                        fragmentation.

        @{b}° MFormat 1.8a@{ub} - Replacement for CBM's "Format" command.  Has a 
                         complete GUI, configurable device filter, can 
                         install a bootable bootblock, etc...

        @{b}° NewIcons V4.1@{ub} - Replaces the icon system with a new one that
                          allows icons to have palette information stored 
                          in them, and to be properly remapped no matter 
                          what's your WB palette, and still more.

        @{b}° TDPrefs 1.0@{ub} - Preferences editor for trackdisk.device, can 
                        adjust the step rate, disable the drive click, 
                        etc...

        @{b}° XPKatana 1.2 @{ub} - GUI/ARexx interface for the XPK packing system,
                         let's you (un)pack files using standard XPK
                         libraries, can also unpack files packed with alien
                         formats through xfdmaster.library.
@endnode
